Civic rights groups say President Jacob Zuma is obliged to suspend NPA head Shaun Abrahams, but he has failed to act. JOHANNESBURG - President Jacob Zuma's lawyer has argued the application aimed at forcing him to suspend National Prosecuting Authority head Shaun Abrahams is premature.#Abrahams Unterhalter: Zuma must be forced to make a decision, there&#39;s a delay here &amp; route Zuma has taken is unlawful, he needs to act. GN Advocate Ishmail Semenya has argued that the president is following procedural fairness and that the arguments made by Freedom Under Law and the Helen Suzman Foundation are unnecessary. The civic rights groups say Zuma is obliged to suspend Abrahams, but he has failed to act. #Abrahams Unterhalter says Zuma has given the 3 until Monday to respond but hasn&#39;t indicated when he will make a decision about inquiry. GNThey also want advocates Torie Pretorius and Sibongile Mzinyathi to be suspended over their handling of the prosecution of Finance Minister Pravin Gordhan.WATCH: NPA issues Gordhan with summons for fraud(Edited by Shimoney Regter)